## Appendix B: Scaling Analysis

**Retrieval Performance at Scale:**

| Memory Count | Index Size | Query Latency (p99) | Strategy |
|---|---|---|---|
| 10K | ~150 MB | <10ms | Single HNSW + keyword |
| 100K | ~1.5 GB | <25ms | Multi-index with query planning |
| 1M | ~15 GB | <50ms | Tiered indices (hot/warm/cold split) |
| 10M | ~150 GB | <100ms | Hierarchical HNSW + query routing + cluster pre-filtering |
| 100M | ~1.5 TB | <200ms | Distributed indices + approximate nearest neighbor with re-ranking |

**Storage Requirements:**

| Scenario | Annual Growth | 80-Year Total | Strategy |
|---|---|---|---|
| Conservative (text only) | ~500 MB | ~40 GB | Single device |
| Moderate (text + metadata) | ~2 GB | ~160 GB | Local + cloud backup |
| Rich (multimodal) | ~20 GB | ~1.6 TB | Tiered storage (hot SSD + cold HDD + archive) |
| Ambient capture | ~200 GB | ~16 TB | Aggressive compression + cloud tiering + selective retention |

**Dream Engine Performance Budget:**

| Phase | Time Budget | Scaling |
|---|---|---|
| Consolidation (near-dup detection) | 5 min | O(n log n) via LSH |
| Hebbian update | 1 min | O(sessions × avg_retrievals) |
| Pattern discovery | 10 min | O(n) Louvain + O(clusters²) bridge detection |
| Contradiction detection | 5 min | O(high-confidence semantic pairs) |
| Decay processing | 2 min | O(n) scan |
| Anticipatory loading | 2 min | O(calendar_events × prediction_model) |
| Schema evolution | 5 min | O(clusters) |
| **Total** | **~30 min** | Fits in idle time for up to ~1M memories |

